---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About | RicePattyJulls">

  <nav class="lab-nav">
    <div class="lab-nav-crumbs">
      <a class="lab-nav-brand" href="/">HOME</a>
      <span class="lab-nav-sep">/</span>
      <span class="lab-nav-current">ABOUT</span>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <section class="hero section-block">
    <span class="eyebrow">Offensive Security Practitioner</span>
    <h1 class="hero-title">About</h1>
    <p class="hero-copy">
      Red team operator and offensive security researcher focused on identity attacks,
      cloud privilege escalation, and Active Directory exploitation. This site is an
      operator notebook — built from lab work, certification material, and hands-on
      offensive research. Not a showcase of compliance deliverables.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <section class="section-block">
    <span class="section-tag">Focus Areas</span>
    <div class="hero-stats" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div class="card stat-card hot">
        <p class="stat-value">AD</p>
        <span class="stat-label">Kerberos · Delegation · Trust Abuse</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card stat-card hot">
        <p class="stat-value">Entra ID</p>
        <span class="stat-label">Token Tradecraft · Graph · ARM</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card stat-card">
        <p class="stat-value">Cloud</p>
        <span class="stat-label">Privilege Escalation · Identity Abuse</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card stat-card">
        <p class="stat-value">Web</p>
        <span class="stat-label">Auth Bypass · Logic Flaws · API Abuse</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <section class="section-block">
    <span class="section-tag">Certifications</span>
    <div class="grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); margin-top: 1.5rem;">

      <div class="card" style="padding: 1.5rem;">
        <span class="index-badge" style="display:inline-block; margin-bottom: .75rem;">CRTO</span>
        <h3 class="path-title" style="margin-bottom: .5rem;">Certified Red Team Operator</h3>
        <p style="font-size: .9rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--muted, #888);">
          Red team operations against Windows environments. C2 infrastructure, OPSEC, Active Directory
          exploitation end-to-end — credential access, lateral movement, domain dominance,
          and evasion against modern defenses.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="padding: 1.5rem;">
        <span class="index-badge" style="display:inline-block; margin-bottom: .75rem;">CRTM</span>
        <h3 class="path-title" style="margin-bottom: .5rem;">Certified Red Team Master</h3>
        <p style="font-size: .9rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--muted, #888);">
          Advanced red team techniques. Complex trust abuse, MSSQL lateral movement chains,
          cross-forest pivoting, advanced evasion, and post-exploitation across segmented environments.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card" style="padding: 1.5rem;">
        <span class="index-badge" style="display:inline-block; margin-bottom: .75rem;">CARTE</span>
        <h3 class="path-title" style="margin-bottom: .5rem;">Certified Azure Red Team Expert</h3>
        <p style="font-size: .9rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--muted, #888);">
          Azure and Entra ID offensive operations. Token theft, Graph and ARM abuse, Key Vault
          exploitation, Managed Identity abuse, hybrid attack paths, and cross-tenant pivoting.
          The primary source for the Azure section of this site.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-divider"></div>

  <section class="section-block">
    <span class="section-tag">What This Site Is</span>
    <div class="card" style="padding: 1.75rem; max-width: 760px;">
      <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        An operator notebook built from real lab work — Active Directory attack paths from CRTO and CRTM,
        Entra ID and Azure techniques from CARTE, and web exploitation research from ongoing practice.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        Every technique documented here has been validated in a lab environment. The content is sanitized —
        no live credential material, no exam-specific identifiers, no raw writeups — but the attack logic
        is real and operator-usable.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.75;">
        The focus is identity and cloud: Active Directory trust abuse, Entra ID token tradecraft,
        Azure privilege escalation chains, and the hybrid paths that connect them. Web exploitation
        is a parallel track. No compliance content, no defensive posturing, no marketing copy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="footer-note">
    <span>Offensive Security · Identity · Cloud · Active Directory</span>
    <a href="/#contact" style="color: var(--accent);">Get in touch →</a>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
